# Project Structure

## Root Directory Structure
- [src/](mdc:src): Main source code directory
  - [app/](mdc:src/app): Next.js application routes and pages
  - [components/](mdc:src/components): Reusable React components
  - [hooks/](mdc:src/hooks): Custom React hooks
  - [lib/](mdc:src/lib): Utility functions and shared libraries
  - [ai/](mdc:src/ai): AI-related functionality

## Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json): Project dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json): TypeScript configuration
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts): Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts): Tailwind CSS configuration
- [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs): PostCSS configuration
- [components.json](mdc:components.json): UI components configuration
- [.cursor/mcp.json](mdc:.cursor/mcp.json): MCP server configurations

## Documentation
- [docs/](mdc:docs): Project documentation
- [README.md](mdc:README.md): Project overview and setup instructions
- [.cursor/rules/](mdc:.cursor/rules): Cursor AI assistance rules

## Build and Development
- [.next/](mdc:.next): Next.js build output
- [node_modules/](mdc:node_modules): Project dependencies
- [next-env.d.ts](mdc:next-env.d.ts): Next.js TypeScript declarations

## Version Control
- [.gitignore](mdc:.gitignore): Git ignore patterns
- [.git/](mdc:.git): Git repository data

This is a Next.js TypeScript project using:
- Next.js for the framework
- TypeScript for type safety
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- PostCSS for CSS processing
- Custom components configuration

## Rules
The `.cursor/rules` directory contains markdown files (`.mdc`) that provide guidance to the AI about:
- Project structure
- Configuration settings
- Development conventions
- File relationships

Each rule file uses Markdown format with Cursor-specific extensions for file references.



